    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-05-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-05-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="472"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d472">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51W89 Rumania/201</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Under Secretary of State</hi> (<hi
                        rend="italic">Phillips</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-05-24">May 24,
                            1934</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Rumanian Minister<note n="71" xml:id="d472fn71">Charles A. Davila.</note>
                    said that he had noticed in the publicity given out following the Attorney
                    General’s decision<note n="72" xml:id="d472fn72">See footnote 20, <ref
                            target="#pg_540">p. 540</ref>.</note> with respect to “token” payments
                    that Rumania was not included among those countries which had made “token”
                    payments. He pointed out that his government had in fact made a payment on
                    account during the last year and that he was even now discussing with his
                    government the payment due on the Hoover Moratorium;<note n="73"
                        xml:id="d472fn73">See <hi rend="italic">Annual Report of the Secretary of
                            the Treasury</hi>, 1932, p. 305.</note> that his government had offered
                    a payment of $4,000 which he regarded as too little and which he was seeking to
                    raise to $8,000. It was merely a question, he said, of reaching a decision in
                    this respect, and he asked, therefore, that in any debt message which the
                    President might have in mind sending to Congress Rumania would not be classed
                    among those who were actually in default at the present moment.</p>
                <pb facs="0692" n="592" xml:id="pg_592"/>
                <p>I said that I would look into the subject and see if anything could be done.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
